[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/FreeRDP/winpr/include/winpr/[0m[95mstream.h[0m:[1;92m703:3[0m in Stream_Read                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         An AddressSanitizer report has detected a heap-buffer-overflow during the parsing   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         of a client network data block. An [1;36m8[0m-byte write occurs immediately past the end of  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         a [1;36m992[0m-byte heap allocation. The invalid write is performed in the function          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `Stream_Read` when invoked by `gcc_read_client_network_data`.                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Issue                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           A write of eight bytes is made to an address that lies exactly one byte past the  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         end of a heap buffer. The buffer in question is allocated via `calloc` in `mcs_new` [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         for handling an MCS [1m([0mMultipoint Communication Service[1m)[0m create request. The overflow [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         is detected at the call site of `Stream_Read` in `winpr/stream.h:[1;36m703[0m`.              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Vulnerability type                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           This is a heap-buffer-overflow, specifically an out-of-bounds write on the heap.  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Key observations                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m1[0m. The corrupted buffer spans [1;36m992[0m bytes [1m([0m`[1m[[0m[1;36m0x519000001980[0m, [1;36m0x519000001d60[0m[1m)[0m`[1m)[0m.     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m2[0m. The overflow occurs at offset [1;36m992[0m [1m([0mthe very end of the buffer[1m)[0m when            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `Stream_Read` attempts to write eight bytes.                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m3[0m. The call chain leading to the overflow is:                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `Stream_Read` [1m([0m`stream.h:[1;36m703[0m`[1m)[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `gcc_read_client_network_data` [1m([0m`gcc.[1;92mc:1875[0m`[1m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `gcc_read_client_data_blocks` [1m([0m`gcc.[1;92mc:617[0m`[1m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `gcc_read_conference_create_request` [1m([0m`gcc.[1;92mc:414[0m`[1m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `mcs_recv_connect_initial` [1m([0m`mcs.[1;92mc:700[0m`[1m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request` [1m([0m`freerdp.[1;92mc:1441[0m`[1m)[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `test_server` [35m/[0m fuzz harness [1m([0m`TestFuzzCoreServer.c`[1m)[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m4[0m. The heap allocation is performed in `mcs_new` [1m([0m`mcs.[1;92mc:1446[0m`[1m)[0m via `calloc`,     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         which sets up data structures for MCS.                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Code areas to investigate                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           To fully understand the context and root of the overflow, review the following    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         modules and functions:                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • winpr/stream.h – implementation of `Stream_Read` and related buffer-management  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         routines                                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m           • libfreerdp/core/mcs.c – MCS initialization in `mcs_new` and MCS connect request [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         handling in `mcs_recv_connect_initial`                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • libfreerdp/core/freerdp.c – validation entry point in                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request`                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • libfreerdp/core/test/TestFuzzCoreServer.c – fuzzing harness that triggers the   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         An AddressSanitizer report revealed a heap-buffer-overflow in the inline function   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `Stream_Read` [1m([0mwinpr/include/winpr/stream.h[1m)[0m when reading [1;36m8[0m bytes past the end of   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         an allocated [1;36m992[0m-byte buffer. The overflow is triggered during processing of an MCS [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         connect-initial PDU in FreeRDP’s GCC handling code. A patch was attempted to        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         strengthen the pre-read assertion by replacing `[1;35mStream_GetRemainingCapacity[0m[1m([0m_s[1m)[0m`    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         with `[1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1m([0m_s[1m)[0m`. After applying the patch, the sanitizer still [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         reports the same out-of-bounds write in `Stream_Read`, indicating the underlying    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         overflow remains unaddressed.                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - AddressSanitizer: `heap-buffer-overflow` on a write of size [1;36m8[0m at the exact end [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         of a [1;36m992[0m-byte region.                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Faulting instruction in `Stream_Read` [1m([0mstream.h:[1;36m703[0m[1m)[0m, invoked from             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `gcc_read_client_network_data` → `gcc_read_client_data_blocks` →                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `gcc_read_conference_create_request` → `mcs_recv_connect_initial` →                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request`.                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The buffer was allocated via `calloc` in `mcs_new` with a total size of [1;36m992[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         bytes; a subsequent `memcpy` writes beyond that boundary.                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Important observations                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The overflow occurs when `Stream_Read` copies data from `_s->pointer` without  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         catching the boundary violation.                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The sanitizer trace shows the overflow target address equals `base + [1;36m992[0m`,     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         i.e., zero bytes past the allocated region.                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The call stack roots in the fuzzing harness [1m([0m`TestFuzzCoreServer.c`[1m)[0m but the   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         overflow is in production code [1m([0m`winpr/stream.h`, `gcc.c`, `mcs.c`[1m)[0m.                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - File modified: winpr/include/winpr/stream.h                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Original lines around Stream_Read:                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1m([0m_b || [1m([0m_n == [1;36m0[0m[1m)[0m[1m)[0m;                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1m([0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingCapacity[0m[1m([0m_s[1m)[0m >= _n[1m)[0m;                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1;35mmemcpy[0m[1m([0m_b, [1m([0m_s->pointer[1m)[0m, [1m([0m_n[1m)[0m[1m)[0m;                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Patched lines:                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1m([0m_b || [1m([0m_n == [1;36m0[0m[1m)[0m[1m)[0m;                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1m([0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1m([0m_s[1m)[0m >= _n[1m)[0m;                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1;35mmemcpy[0m[1m([0m_b, [1m([0m_s->pointer[1m)[0m, [1m([0m_n[1m)[0m[1m)[0m;                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The change replaces the capacity check with a length-based check, aiming to    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ensure that the requested read does not exceed the stream’s remaining data length.  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Post-patch result                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A nearly identical AddressSanitizer error persists in `Stream_Read` at the     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         same address and call stack.                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The overflow still occurs when copying [1;36m8[0m bytes at the end of the allocated     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         buffer, indicating the new assertion does not prevent or detect the out-of-bounds   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         copy.                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. Areas for further investigation                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The implementation of `Stream_GetRemainingLength` versus                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `Stream_GetRemainingCapacity` and their intended semantics.                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - How and where the stream’s buffer size, length, and capacity are               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         initialized—particularly in `mcs_new` and any stream setup routines.                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The code paths in `gcc_read_client_network_data` and                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `gcc_read_client_data_blocks` that lead to the out-of-bounds read, including any    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         block-size or count fields parsed from the input.                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The boundaries checked by the higher-level MCS and GCC parsers                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`mcs_recv_connect_initial`, `gcc_read_conference_create_request`[1m)[0m to ensure they   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         match the actual buffer allocations.                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Any adjacent inline functions in `winpr/stream.h` that update `pointer`,       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `length`, or `capacity` [1m([0me.g., `Stream_Seek`, `Stream_SetPosition`[1m)[0m.                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer‐reported heap‐buffer‐overflow occurring in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe inline function Stream_Read [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwinpr/include/winpr/stream.h[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when reading client [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata in the GCC module of FreeRDP. The overflow happens [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes past a [0m[1;36m992[0m[39m‐byte [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer allocated by mcs_new, on an [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m‐byte write.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch was attempted that replaces the existing assertion on remaining capacity [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith a runtime boundary check:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39m_s->pointer + _n[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_s->buffer + _s->capacity[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore calling memcpy. After applying this patch, the same heap‐buffer‐overflow in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStream_Read is still reported by AddressSanitizer at the same code location.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer log reports a WRITE of size [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m at address [0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…1d60 in Stream_Read [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mstream.h:[0m[1;36m703[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- That address is exactly [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes beyond a [0m[1;36m992[0m[39m‐byte region [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m1980[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…1d60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated via calloc in mcs_new.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Call stack: Stream_Read → gcc_read_client_network_data → [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgcc_read_client_data_blocks → gcc_read_conference_create_request → [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmcs_recv_connect_initial → freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request → test_server → [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLLVMFuzzerTestOneInput → FuzzerLoop.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow indicates Stream_Read invoked memcpy with a size that extended past [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe end of the underlying buffer.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In winpr/include/winpr/stream.h, the three assertions guarding the memcpy were [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreduced to a single assert on the destination pointer, and a manual bounds check [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas added immediately before memcpy:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39m_b || [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_n == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Prevent read beyond the end of the allocated buffer *[0m[35m/[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39m_s->pointer + _n[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_s->buffer + _s->capacity[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39m_b, [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_s->pointer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_n[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mStream_Seek[0m[1;39m([0m[39m_s, _n[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The original assertions [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincluding one on remaining capacity[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m were removed to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallow compilation but guard at runtime.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResult After Patch  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer still reports a heap‐buffer‐overflow in Stream_Read [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow at [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstream.h:[0m[1;92m705:9[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow address, call stack, and allocation region remain unchanged.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The internal layout of wStream [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmembers pointer, buffer, capacity[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and how [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStream_GetRemainingCapacity is computed.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The behavior of Stream_Seek and whether repeated reads can move pointer beyond [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All call sites of Stream_Read in the GCC parsing code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcore/gcc.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to see how [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread sizes are determined.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The allocation logic in mcs_new and any assumptions about buffer size vs data to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe read.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Whether additional boundary checks or length validations are required upstream of[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[35m/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/[0m[95mlibc.so.6+0x24082[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mBuildId: [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m5792732f783158c66fb4f3756458ca24e46e827d[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: __interceptor_calloc--mcs_new--freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/FreeRDP/winpr/include/winpr/[0m[95mstream.h[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m703:3[0m[39m in Stream_Read[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer report revealed a heap-buffer-overflow in the function [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStream_Read [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwinpr/include/winpr/stream.h[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when processing a client “conference [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcreate” request in FreeRDP’s GCC handling code. A patch was attempted to harden [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStream_Seek and Stream_Read with explicit boundary checks and logging, and to add [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcapacity checks before reading channel names and options in [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgcc_read_client_network_data [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlibfreerdp/core/gcc.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. After applying the patch, the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuild fails with compilation errors: `STREAM_TAG` is used in the new logging calls [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut is not declared, causing multiple errors in winpr stream-related headers.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer output reports a write of [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes just past a [0m[1;36m992[0m[39m-byte heap [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation during the call to Stream_Read in stream.h:[0m[1;36m703[0m[39m.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow occurs in the context of reading client network data:  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Stream_Read → gcc_read_client_network_data → gcc_read_client_data_blocks → [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgcc_read_conference_create_request → mcs_recv_connect_initial → [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request → test_server → LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The allocated buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0x519000001980[0m[39m – [0m[1;36m0x519000001d60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is exactly [0m[1;36m992[0m[39m bytes; [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe code attempts to read more than the remaining capacity.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In winpr/include/winpr/stream.h:  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Stream_Seek: Replace an assert on remaining capacity with a run-time check. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIf the requested offset exceeds remaining capacity, log an error [0m[1;39m([0m[39musing WLog_ERR [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand STREAM_TAG[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and clamp `s->pointer` to the buffer end.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Stream_Read: Replace the assert on remaining capacity with a similar check; [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon underflow, log via [0m[1;35mWLog_ERR[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSTREAM_TAG[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and return early. Otherwise perform [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemcpy and advance the pointer.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In libfreerdp/core/gcc.c around line [0m[1;36m1875[0m[39m:  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Before reading the channel name [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mStream_Read[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, channel->Name, [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCHANNEL_NAME_LEN + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, check `[0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingCapacity[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. Return FALSE on [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderflow.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Similarly guard `[0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT32[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, channel->options[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with a capacity [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Result and Build Errors  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compilation fails when including the modified stream.h:  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     “use of undeclared identifier ‘STREAM_TAG’” at both modified locations in [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstream.h [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m130[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m716[0m[39m in the patch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These errors surface in multiple translation units that include winpr/stream.h[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., crypto/crypto.c, ObjectPool.c, MessageQueue.c, ArrayList.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSTREAM_TAG is not defined anywhere in the scope of that header.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logging infrastructure in WinPR:  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Determine where and how logging tags [0m[1;39m([0m[39msuch as STREAM_TAG[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are normally [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefined.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Check if stream.c or a related header defines STREAM_TAG or if a different [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtag macro should be used.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Usage of Stream_Read and Stream_Seek across the codebase:  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Identify all callers of Stream_Read and Stream_Seek to assess if unified [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboundary checks or assertions should be placed elsewhere.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The GCC client data parsing functions in libfreerdp/core/gcc.c:  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Review all Stream_Read* calls to ensure consistent capacity checks.  [0m        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlong[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[35m/src/llvm-project/compiler-rt/lib/fuzzer/[0m[95mFuzzerDriver.cpp[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m327:6[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x55991b30ce0f[0m[39m in fuzzer::[0m[1;35mFuzzerDriver[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint*, char***, int [0m[1;39m([0m[39m*[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned char [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconst*, unsigned long[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/llvm-project/compiler-rt/lib/fuzzer/[0m[95mFuzzerDriver.cpp[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m862:9[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x55991b3380b2[0m[39m in main [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/llvm-project/compiler-rt/lib/fuzzer/[0m[95mFuzzerMain.cpp[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m20:10[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m9[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x7fab65854082[0m[39m in __libc_start_main [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[35m/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/[0m[95mlibc.so.6+0x24082[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mBuildId: [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m5792732f783158c66fb4f3756458ca24e46e827d[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: __interceptor_calloc--mcs_new--freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/FreeRDP/winpr/include/winpr/[0m[95mstream.h[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m703:3[0m[39m in Stream_Read[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer-detected heap‐buffer‐overflow in the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction Stream_Read [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwinpr/include/winpr/stream.h:[0m[1;36m703[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, triggered when the fuzzer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexercises `gcc_read_client_network_data` in FreeRDP’s GCC module. A heap buffer of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m992[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallocated in `mcs_new`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is overrun by an [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte write at its boundary.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempt augments Stream_Read and Stream_Seek with explicit [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremaining‐capacity checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlogging an error and returning early if a read or seek [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequest exceeds the buffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and adds similar checks before reading channel names [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand options in `gcc_read_client_network_data` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlibfreerdp/core/gcc.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, AddressSanitizer still reports the same [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow at the [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnewly shifted[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Stream_Read location, indicating that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe overflow path was not fully guarded by the added checks.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer log reports a WRITE of size [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m at `[0m[1;36m0x519000001d60[0m[39m`, exactly at [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe end of a [0m[1;36m992[0m[39m-byte region `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x519000001980[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x519000001d60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow happens inside Stream_Read at line [0m[1;36m703[0m[39m of `stream.h`, called by [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`gcc_read_client_network_data` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgcc.[0m[1;92mc:1875[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m as part of a fuzzer harness.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflowing region was allocated via `calloc` in `mcs_new`, so the stream’s [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcapacity is [0m[1;36m992[0m[39m bytes. The code attempts to read or write beyond that capacity.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace shows the overflow propagating through multiple FreeRDP core [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctions up to the fuzzer entry point.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. In `winpr/include/winpr/stream.h`:  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Wrapped Stream_Seek in a block that checks `[0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingCapacity[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` ≥ [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`_offset`, logs an error if not, clips the pointer to `buffer+capacity`, and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturns.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Wrapped Stream_Read similarly: compute remaining capacity, if it’s less than [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`_n` log an error and return without doing the memcpy or seek.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. In `libfreerdp/core/gcc.c`:  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before calling `[0m[1;35mStream_Read[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, channel->Name, CHANNEL_NAME_LEN + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, check [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingCapacity[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` against `CHANNEL_NAME_LEN + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`; return FALSE on [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailure.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before `[0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT32[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, channel->options[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, check remaining capacity [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT32[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`; return FALSE on failure.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResult After Patch  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The new ASAN output still reports a heap-buffer-overflow at Stream_Read in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`stream.h` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow at line [0m[1;36m724[0m[39m after the patch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The write of size [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m remains at the same address range, indicating that the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow path in Stream_Read was still executed and the memcpy was not bypassed.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The allocation and overflow addresses match the original report, confirming that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnone of the added checks prevented this specific call to memcpy.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All callers of Stream_Read [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand related macros like Stream_Read_UINT32[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`libfreerdp/core/gcc.c` and other modules to ensure correct bounds checks precede [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mevery read.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The implementation of `Stream_GetRemainingCapacity` and the initialization of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`wStream`’s `buffer`, `pointer`, and `capacity` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mespecially in `mcs_new`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Verify [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhether `capacity` accurately reflects the available data region.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Other parsing loops in `gcc_read_client_data_blocks`, [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`gcc_read_conference_create_request`, and `mcs_recv_connect_initial` to identify [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many reads that still lack proper boundary validation.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Potential off-by-one or incorrect length assumptions when reading fixed-size [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfields [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., channel names, options, variable-length client data blocks[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Consistency between the size of the allocated stream buffer and the maximum [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcumulative sizes of all reads performed by the GCC module.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
